In mixer bowl, with the whisk attachment, whisk together the sour cream, eggs, sugar, lemon zest and vanilla until smooth.  Dis-
tribute the rhubarb (which has been squeezed out of excess moisture if frozen then thawed) evenly in pie shells.  Bake in a pre-
heated 325° convection oven for about 45 minutes, until custard is set and shells are golden brown.  Rotate after 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° if they are getting too dark on top.  Remove from oven, cool, then refrigerate.
